{"word":"γαμίζω","slug":"γαμίζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>γαμίζω</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:γάμος\">γάμος</a></el>] <b><i>give</i></b> (a woman) <b><i>in marriage</i></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ act.\">act.</a> <b><a href='B:470 24:38'>Mt 24:38</a>; <a href='B:480 12:25'>Mk 12:25</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a>;</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pass.\">pass.</a> <i>be</i> <i>given in marriage, be married</i> <b><a href='B:470 22:30'>Mt 22:30</a>; <a href='B:480 12:25'>Mk 12:25</a>; <a href='B:490 17:27'>Lk 17:27</a>; <a href='B:490 20:35'>20:35</a>.—<a href='B:530 7:38'>1 Cor 7:38</a></b> poses a special problem: here γ. seems to = <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:γαμέω\">γαμέω</a></el> in the general sense of <i>marry.</i> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:γαμέω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:γαμίσκω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}